68/** Chooses a method for actors to update overlap state (objects it is touching) on initialization, currently only used during level streaming. */
69UENUM(BlueprintType)
70enum class EActorUpdateOverlapsMethod : uint8
71{
72 // Use the default value specified by the native class or config value.
73 UseConfigDefault,
74 // Always update overlap state on initialization.
75 AlwaysUpdate,
76 // Only update if root component has Movable mobility.
77 OnlyUpdateMovable,
78 // Never update overlap state on initialization.
79 NeverUpdate
80};
81
82/** Determines how the transform being passed into actor spawning methods interact with the actor's default root component */
83UENUM(BlueprintType)
84enum class ESpawnActorScaleMethod : uint8
85{
86 /** Ignore the default scale in the actor's root component and hard-set it to the value of SpawnTransform Parameter */
87 OverrideRootScale UMETA(DisplayName = "Override Root Component Scale"),
88 /** Multiply value of the SpawnTransform Parameter with the default scale in the actor's root component */
89 MultiplyWithRoot UMETA(DisplayName = "Multiply Scale With Root Component Scale"),
90 SelectDefaultAtRuntime UMETA(Hidden),
91};
92
93/** Determines in what type of LevelInstance the actor is in, if any. */
94UENUM()
95enum class ELevelInstanceType : uint8
96{
97 None,
98 LevelInstance,
99 LevelInstanceEdit,
100 LevelInstancePropertyOverride
101};
102
103UENUM()
104enum class ELevelInstanceFlags : uint8
105{
106 None = 0,
107 /** Actor is inside an Level Instance editing hierarchy (used to show post process effect) */
108 IsInEditHierarchy = 1,
109 /** Actor has property overrides applied */
110 HasPropertyOverrides = 2,
111 /** Actor has property overrides from a top level editable level instance */
112 HasEditablePropertyOverrides = 4
113};
114
115ENUM_CLASS_FLAGS(ELevelInstanceFlags)

118/** Enum defining how actor will be placed in the partition */
119UENUM()
120enum class UE_DEPRECATED(5.0, "EActorGridPlacement is deprecated.") EActorGridPlacement : uint8
121{
122 // Actor uses its bounds to determine in which runtime cells it's going to be placed.
123 Bounds,
124 // Actor uses its location to determine in which runtime cells it's going to be placed.
125 Location,
126 // Actor is always loaded (not placed in the grid), also affects editor.
127 AlwaysLoaded,
128 None UMETA(Hidden)
129};

132/** Helper struct that allows UPrimitiveComponent and FPrimitiveSceneInfo write to the Actor's LastRenderTime member */
133struct FActorLastRenderTime
134{
135 UE_DEPRECATED(5.6, "Use GetLastRenderTime/SetLastRenderTime instead.")
136 std::atomic<float> LastRenderTime;
137
138 void SetLastRenderTime(float InLastRenderTime)
139 {
140 PRAGMA_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
141 LastRenderTime.store(InLastRenderTime, std::memory_order_relaxed);
142 PRAGMA_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
143 }
144
145 float GetLastRenderTime() const
146 {
147 PRAGMA_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
148 return LastRenderTime.load(std::memory_order_relaxed);
149 PRAGMA_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
150 }
151
152 std::atomic_int32_t NumAlwaysVisibleComponents = 0;
153
154private:
155 static void Set(AActor* InActor, float LastRenderTime);
156 static FActorLastRenderTime* GetPtr(AActor* InActor);
157
158 friend class UPrimitiveComponent;
159 friend struct FPrimitiveSceneInfoAdapter;
160};

194/**
195 * TInlineComponentArray is simply a TArray that reserves a fixed amount of space on the stack
196 * to try to avoid heap allocation when there are fewer than a specified number of elements expected in the result.
197 */
198template<class T, uint32 NumElements = NumInlinedActorComponents>
199class TInlineComponentArray : public TArray<T, TInlineAllocator<NumElements>>
200{
201 typedef TArray<T, TInlineAllocator<NumElements>> Super;
202
203public:
204 TInlineComponentArray() : Super() { }
205 TInlineComponentArray(const AActor* Actor, bool bIncludeFromChildActors = false);
206};
207
208template<class T, uint32 NumElements>
209struct TIsContiguousContainer<TInlineComponentArray<T, NumElements>>
210{
211 enum { Value = true };
212};

214/**
215 * Actor is the base class for an Object that can be placed or spawned in a level.
216 * Actors may contain a collection of ActorComponents, which can be used to control how actors move, how they are rendered, etc.
217 * The other main function of an Actor is the replication of properties and function calls across the network during play.
218 *
219 *
220 * Actor initialization has multiple steps, here's the order of important virtual functions that get called:
221 * - UObject::PostLoad: For actors statically placed in a level, the normal UObject PostLoad gets called both in the editor and during gameplay.
222 * This is not called for newly spawned actors.
223 * - UActorComponent::OnComponentCreated: When an actor is spawned in the editor or during gameplay, this gets called for any native components.
224 * For blueprint-created components, this gets called during construction for that component.
225 * This is not called for components loaded from a level.
226 * - AActor::PreRegisterAllComponents: For statically placed actors and spawned actors that have native root components, this gets called now.
227 * For blueprint actors without a native root component, these registration functions get called later during construction.
228 * - UActorComponent::RegisterComponent: All components are registered in editor and at runtime, this creates their physical/visual representation.
229 * These calls may be distributed over multiple frames, but are always after PreRegisterAllComponents.
230 * This may also get called later on after an UnregisterComponent call removes it from the world.
231 * - AActor::PostRegisterAllComponents: Called for all actors both in the editor and in gameplay, this is the last function that is called in all cases.
232 * - AActor::PostActorCreated: When an actor is created in the editor or during gameplay, this gets called right before construction.
233 * This is not called for components loaded from a level.
234 * - AActor::UserConstructionScript: Called for blueprints that implement a construction script.
235 * - AActor::OnConstruction: Called at the end of ExecuteConstruction, which calls the blueprint construction script.
236 * This is called after all blueprint-created components are fully created and registered.
237 * This is only called during gameplay for spawned actors, and may get rerun in the editor when changing blueprints.
238 * - AActor::PreInitializeComponents: Called before InitializeComponent is called on the actor's components.
239 * This is only called during gameplay and in certain editor preview windows.
240 * - UActorComponent::Activate: This will be called only if the component has bAutoActivate set.
241 * It will also got called later on if a component is manually activated.
242 * - UActorComponent::InitializeComponent: This will be called only if the component has bWantsInitializeComponentSet.
243 * This only happens once per gameplay session.
244 * - AActor::PostInitializeComponents: Called after the actor's components have been initialized, only during gameplay and some editor previews.
245 * - AActor::BeginPlay: Called when the level starts ticking, only during actual gameplay.
246 * This normally happens right after PostInitializeComponents but can be delayed for networked or child actors.
247 *
248 * @see https://docs.unrealengine.com/Programming/UnrealArchitecture/Actors
249 * @see https://docs.unrealengine.com/Programming/UnrealArchitecture/Actors/ActorLifecycle
250 * @see UActorComponent
251 */
252UCLASS(BlueprintType, Blueprintable, MigratingAsset, config=Engine, meta=(ShortTooltip="An Actor is an object that can be placed or spawned in the world."), MinimalAPI)

389 /** If true, the actor belongs to a level instance which is currently in an edit mode: edit or property override edit */
390 bool IsInAnyEditLevelInstance() const
391 {
392 return IsInEditLevelInstance() || IsInPropertyOverrideLevelInstance();
393 }
394
395 /** If true, the actor belongs to a level instance which is currently being edited */
396 bool IsInEditLevelInstance() const
397 {
398 return LevelInstanceType == ELevelInstanceType::LevelInstanceEdit;
399 }
400
401 /** If true, the actor belongs to a level instance which is currently in property override edit */
402 bool IsInPropertyOverrideLevelInstance() const
403 {
404 return LevelInstanceType == ELevelInstanceType::LevelInstancePropertyOverride;
405 }

407 /** If true, the actor belongs to a level instance which is currently being edited or a parent level instance being edited. */

413 /** If true, this actor or one of its components has property overrides applied. */

417 }
418
419 /** If true, this actor or one of its components has property overrides applied from an editable level instance (level instance is in a non readonly level) */
420 bool HasEditableLevelLevelInstancePropertyOverrides() const
421 {
422 return EnumHasAnyFlags(LevelInstanceFlags, ELevelInstanceFlags::HasEditablePropertyOverrides);
423 }
424
425 /** If true, the actor belongs to a level instance. */
426 bool IsInLevelInstance() const
427 {
428 return LevelInstanceType != ELevelInstanceType::None;
429 }

647 /** Whether to use use the async physics tick with this actor. */

649 uint8 bAsyncPhysicsTickEnabled : 1;
650
651 /**
652 * Condition for calling UpdateOverlaps() to initialize overlap state when loaded in during level streaming.
653 * If set to 'UseConfigDefault', the default specified in ini (displayed in 'DefaultUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming') will be used.
654 * If overlaps are not initialized, this actor and attached components will not have an initial state of what objects are touching it,
655 * and overlap events may only come in once one of those objects update overlaps themselves (for example when moving).
656 * However if an object touching it *does* initialize state, both objects will know about their touching state with each other.
657 * This can be a potentially large performance savings during level loading and streaming, and is safe if the object and others initially
658 * overlapping it do not need the overlap state because they will not trigger overlap notifications.
659 *
660 * Note that if 'bGenerateOverlapEventsDuringLevelStreaming' is true, overlaps are always updated in this case, but that flag
661 * determines whether the Begin/End overlap events are triggered.
662 *
663 * @see bGenerateOverlapEventsDuringLevelStreaming, DefaultUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming, GetUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming()
664 */
665 UPROPERTY(Category=Collision, EditAnywhere)
666 EActorUpdateOverlapsMethod UpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming;
667
668public:
669
670 /** Get the method used to UpdateOverlaps() when loaded via level streaming. Resolves the 'UseConfigDefault' option to the class default specified in config. */
671 ENGINE_API EActorUpdateOverlapsMethod GetUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming() const;
672
673private:
674
675 /**
676 * Default value taken from config file for this class when 'UseConfigDefault' is chosen for
677 * 'UpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming'. This allows a default to be chosen per class in the matching config.
678 * For example, for Actor it could be specified in DefaultEngine.ini as:
679 *
680 * [/Script/Engine.Actor]
681 * DefaultUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming = OnlyUpdateMovable
682 *
683 * Another subclass could set their default to something different, such as:
684 *
685 * [/Script/Engine.BlockingVolume]
686 * DefaultUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming = NeverUpdate
687 *
688 * @see UpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming
689 */
690 UPROPERTY(Config, Category = Collision, VisibleAnywhere)
691 EActorUpdateOverlapsMethod DefaultUpdateOverlapsMethodDuringLevelStreaming;

1539public:
1540 /**
1541 * Get the actor-to-world transform.
1542 * @return The transform that transforms from actor space to world space.
1543 */
1544 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta=(DisplayName = "Get Actor Transform", ScriptName = "GetActorTransform"), Category="Transformation")
1545 const FTransform& GetTransform() const
1546 {
1547 return ActorToWorld();
1548 }
1549
1550 /** Get the local-to-world transform of the RootComponent. Identical to GetTransform(). */
1551 FORCEINLINE const FTransform& ActorToWorld() const
1552 {
1553 return (RootComponent ? RootComponent->GetComponentTransform() : FTransform::Identity);
1554 }
1555
1556 /** Returns the location of the RootComponent of this Actor */
1557 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta=(DisplayName = "Get Actor Location", ScriptName = "GetActorLocation", Keywords="position"), Category="Transformation")
1558 FVector K2_GetActorLocation() const;
1559
1560 /**
1561 * Move the Actor to the specified location.
1562 * @param NewLocation The new location to move the Actor to.
1563 * @param bSweep Whether we sweep to the destination location, triggering overlaps along the way and stopping short of the target if blocked by something.
1564 * Only the root component is swept and checked for blocking collision, child components move without sweeping. If collision is off, this has no effect.
1565 * @param bTeleport Whether we teleport the physics state (if physics collision is enabled for this object).
1566 * If true, physics velocity for this object is unchanged (so ragdoll parts are not affected by change in location).
1567 * If false, physics velocity is updated based on the change in position (affecting ragdoll parts).
1568 * If CCD is on and not teleporting, this will affect objects along the entire swept volume.
1569 * Note that when teleporting, any child/attached components will be teleported too, maintaining their current offset even if they are being simulated.
1570 * Setting the location without teleporting will not update the location of simulated child/attached components.
1571 * @param SweepHitResult The hit result from the move if swept.
1572 * @return Whether the location was successfully set (if not swept), or whether movement occurred at all (if swept).
1573 */
1574 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta=(DisplayName = "Set Actor Location", ScriptName = "SetActorLocation", Keywords="position"), Category="Transformation")
1575 ENGINE_API bool K2_SetActorLocation(FVector NewLocation, bool bSweep, FHitResult& SweepHitResult, bool bTeleport);
1576
1577 /** Returns rotation of the RootComponent of this Actor. */
1578 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta=(DisplayName = "Get Actor Rotation", ScriptName = "GetActorRotation"), Category="Transformation")
1579 FRotator K2_GetActorRotation() const;
1580
1581 /** Get the forward (X) vector (length 1.0) from this Actor, in world space. */
1582 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category = "Transformation")
1583 FVector GetActorForwardVector() const;
1584
1585 /** Get the up (Z) vector (length 1.0) from this Actor, in world space. */
1586 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category = "Transformation")
1587 FVector GetActorUpVector() const;
1588
1589 /** Get the right (Y) vector (length 1.0) from this Actor, in world space. */
1590 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category = "Transformation")
1591 FVector GetActorRightVector() const;

1594 * Returns the bounding box of all components that make up this Actor (excluding ChildActorComponents).
1595 * @param bOnlyCollidingComponents If true, will only return the bounding box for components with collision enabled.
1596 * @param Origin Set to the center of the actor in world space
1597 * @param BoxExtent Set to half the actor's size in 3d space

1599 */

1608 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category="Transformation")
1609 ENGINE_API virtual FVector GetVelocity() const;

1611 /**
1612 * Move the actor instantly to the specified location.
1613 *
1614 * @param NewLocation The new location to teleport the Actor to.
1615 * @param bSweep Whether we sweep to the destination location, triggering overlaps along the way and stopping short of the target if blocked by something.
1616 * Only the root component is swept and checked for blocking collision, child components move without sweeping. If collision is off, this has no effect.
1617 * @param Teleport How we teleport the physics state (if physics collision is enabled for this object).
1618 * If equal to ETeleportType::TeleportPhysics, physics velocity for this object is unchanged (so ragdoll parts are not affected by change in location).
1619 * If equal to ETeleportType::None, physics velocity is updated based on the change in position (affecting ragdoll parts).
1620 * If CCD is on and not teleporting, this will affect objects along the entire swept volume.
1621 * Note that when teleporting, any child/attached components will be teleported too, maintaining their current offset even if they are being simulated.
1622 * Setting the location without teleporting will not update the location of simulated child/attached components.
1623 * @param OutSweepHitResult The hit result from the move if swept.
1624 * @return Whether the location was successfully set if not swept, or whether movement occurred if swept.
1625 */
1626 ENGINE_API bool SetActorLocation(const FVector& NewLocation, bool bSweep=false, FHitResult* OutSweepHitResult=nullptr, ETeleportType Teleport = ETeleportType::None);
1627
1628 /**
1629 * Set the Actor's rotation instantly to the specified rotation.
1630 *
1631 * @param NewRotation The new rotation for the Actor.
1632 * @param bTeleportPhysics Whether we teleport the physics state (if physics collision is enabled for this object).
1633 * If true, physics velocity for this object is unchanged (so ragdoll parts are not affected by change in location).
1634 * If false, physics velocity is updated based on the change in position (affecting ragdoll parts).
1635 * Note that when teleporting, any child/attached components will be teleported too, maintaining their current offset even if they are being simulated.
1636 * Setting the rotation without teleporting will not update the rotation of simulated child/attached components.
1637 * @return Whether the rotation was successfully set.
1638 */
1639 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta=(DisplayName = "Set Actor Rotation", ScriptName = "SetActorRotation"), Category="Transformation")
1640 ENGINE_API bool K2_SetActorRotation(FRotator NewRotation, bool bTeleportPhysics);
1641
1642 /**
1643 * Set the Actor's rotation instantly to the specified rotation.
1644 *
1645 * @param NewRotation The new rotation for the Actor.
1646 * @param Teleport How we teleport the physics state (if physics collision is enabled for this object).
1647 * If equal to ETeleportType::TeleportPhysics, physics velocity for this object is unchanged (so ragdoll parts are not affected by change in location).
1648 * If equal to ETeleportType::None, physics velocity is updated based on the change in position (affecting ragdoll parts).
1649 * Note that when teleporting, any child/attached components will be teleported too, maintaining their current offset even if they are being simulated.
1650 * Setting the rotation without teleporting will not update the rotation of simulated child/attached components.
1651 * @return Whether the rotation was successfully set.
1652 */
1653 ENGINE_API bool SetActorRotation(FRotator NewRotation, ETeleportType Teleport = ETeleportType::None);
1654 ENGINE_API bool SetActorRotation(const FQuat& NewRotation, ETeleportType Teleport = ETeleportType::None);
1655
1656 /**
1657 * Move the actor instantly to the specified location and rotation.
1658 *
1659 * @param NewLocation The new location to teleport the Actor to.
1660 * @param NewRotation The new rotation for the Actor.
1661 * @param bSweep Whether we sweep to the destination location, triggering overlaps along the way and stopping short of the target if blocked by something.
1662 * Only the root component is swept and checked for blocking collision, child components move without sweeping. If collision is off, this has no effect.
1663 * @param bTeleport Whether we teleport the physics state (if physics collision is enabled for this object).
1664 * If true, physics velocity for this object is unchanged (so ragdoll parts are not affected by change in location).
1665 * If false, physics velocity is updated based on the change in position (affecting ragdoll parts).
1666 * If CCD is on and not teleporting, this will affect objects along the entire swept volume.
1667 * Note that when teleporting, any child/attached components will be teleported too, maintaining their current offset even if they are being simulated.
1668 * Setting the location without teleporting will not update the location of simulated child/attached components.
1669 * @param SweepHitResult The hit result from the move if swept.
1670 * @return Whether the rotation was successfully set.
1671 */
1672 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, Category="Transformation", meta=(DisplayName="Set Actor Location And Rotation", ScriptName="SetActorLocationAndRotation"))
1673 ENGINE_API bool K2_SetActorLocationAndRotation(FVector NewLocation, FRotator NewRotation, bool bSweep, FHitResult& SweepHitResult, bool bTeleport);
1674
1675 /**
1676 * Move the actor instantly to the specified location and rotation.
1677 *
1678 * @param NewLocation The new location to teleport the Actor to.
1679 * @param NewRotation The new rotation for the Actor.
1680 * @param bSweep Whether we sweep to the destination location, triggering overlaps along the way and stopping short of the target if blocked by something.
1681 * Only the root component is swept and checked for blocking collision, child components move without sweeping. If collision is off, this has no effect.
1682 * @param Teleport How we teleport the physics state (if physics collision is enabled for this object).
1683 * If equal to ETeleportType::TeleportPhysics, physics velocity for this object is unchanged (so ragdoll parts are not affected by change in location).
1684 * If equal to ETeleportType::None, physics velocity is updated based on the change in position (affecting ragdoll parts).
1685 * If CCD is on and not teleporting, this will affect objects along the entire swept volume.
1686 * Note that when teleporting, any child/attached components will be teleported too, maintaining their current offset even if they are being simulated.
1687 * Setting the location without teleporting will not update the location of simulated child/attached components.
1688 * @param OutSweepHitResult The hit result from the move if swept.
1689 * @return Whether the rotation was successfully set.
1690 */
1691 ENGINE_API bool SetActorLocationAndRotation(FVector NewLocation, FRotator NewRotation, bool bSweep=false, FHitResult* OutSweepHitResult=nullptr, ETeleportType Teleport = ETeleportType::None);
1692 ENGINE_API bool SetActorLocationAndRotation(FVector NewLocation, const FQuat& NewRotation, bool bSweep=false, FHitResult* OutSweepHitResult=nullptr, ETeleportType Teleport = ETeleportType::None);

1930 /**
1931 * Creates a new component and assigns ownership to the Actor this is
1932 * called for. Automatic attachment causes the first component created to
1933 * become the root, and all subsequent components to be attached under that
1934 * root. When bManualAttachment is set, automatic attachment is
1935 * skipped and it is up to the user to attach the resulting component (or
1936 * set it up as the root) themselves.
1937 *
1938 * @see UK2Node_AddComponent DO NOT CALL MANUALLY - BLUEPRINT INTERNAL USE ONLY (for Add Component nodes)
1939 *
1940 * @param TemplateName The name of the Component Template to use.
1941 * @param bManualAttachment Whether manual or automatic attachment is to be used
1942 * @param RelativeTransform The relative transform between the new component and its attach parent (automatic only)
1943 * @param ComponentTemplateContext Optional UBlueprintGeneratedClass reference to use to find the template in. If null (or not a BPGC), component is sought in this Actor's class
1944 * @param bDeferredFinish Whether or not to immediately complete the creation and registration process for this component. Will be false if there are expose on spawn properties being set
1945 */
1946 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta=(ScriptNoExport, BlueprintInternalUseOnly = "true", DefaultToSelf="ComponentTemplateContext", InternalUseParam="ComponentTemplateContext,bDeferredFinish"))
1947 ENGINE_API UActorComponent* AddComponent(FName TemplateName, bool bManualAttachment, const FTransform& RelativeTransform, const UObject* ComponentTemplateContext, bool bDeferredFinish = false);

2024 * @param SocketName Socket name to attach to, if any

2026 * @param RotationRule How to handle rotation when attaching.
2027 * @param ScaleRule How to handle scale when attaching.
2028 * @param bWeldSimulatedBodies Whether to weld together simulated physics bodies.This transfers the shapes in the welded object into the parent (if simulated), which can result in permanent changes that persist even after subsequently detaching.
2029 * @return Whether the attachment was successful or not
2030 */
2031 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, meta = (DisplayName = "Attach Actor To Actor", ScriptName = "AttachToActor", bWeldSimulatedBodies=true), Category = "Transformation")
2032 ENGINE_API bool K2_AttachToActor(AActor* ParentActor, FName SocketName, EAttachmentRule LocationRule, EAttachmentRule RotationRule, EAttachmentRule ScaleRule, bool bWeldSimulatedBodies);

2272 /**
2273 * Event when this actor bumps into a blocking object, or blocks another actor that bumps into it.
2274 * This could happen due to things like Character movement, using Set Location with 'sweep' enabled, or physics simulation.
2275 * For events when objects overlap (e.g. walking into a trigger) see the 'Overlap' event.
2276 *
2277 * @note For collisions during physics simulation to generate hit events, 'Simulation Generates Hit Events' must be enabled.
2278 * @note When receiving a hit from another object's movement (bSelfMoved is false), the directions of 'Hit.Normal' and 'Hit.ImpactNormal'
2279 * will be adjusted to indicate force from the other object against this object.
2280 */
2281 ENGINE_API virtual void NotifyHit(class UPrimitiveComponent* MyComp, AActor* Other, class UPrimitiveComponent* OtherComp, bool bSelfMoved, FVector HitLocation, FVector HitNormal, FVector NormalImpulse, const FHitResult& Hit);
2282 /**
2283 * Event when this actor bumps into a blocking object, or blocks another actor that bumps into it.
2284 * This could happen due to things like Character movement, using Set Location with 'sweep' enabled, or physics simulation.
2285 * For events when objects overlap (e.g. walking into a trigger) see the 'Overlap' event.
2286 *
2287 * @note For collisions during physics simulation to generate hit events, 'Simulation Generates Hit Events' must be enabled.
2288 * @note When receiving a hit from another object's movement (bSelfMoved is false), the directions of 'Hit.Normal' and 'Hit.ImpactNormal'
2289 * will be adjusted to indicate force from the other object against this object.
2290 * @note NormalImpulse will be filled in for physics-simulating bodies, but will be zero for swept-component blocking collisions.
2291 */
2292 UFUNCTION(BlueprintImplementableEvent, meta=(DisplayName = "Hit"), Category="Collision")
2293 ENGINE_API void ReceiveHit(class UPrimitiveComponent* MyComp, AActor* Other, class UPrimitiveComponent* OtherComp, bool bSelfMoved, FVector HitLocation, FVector HitNormal, FVector NormalImpulse, const FHitResult& Hit);

2449 /** See if this actor is owned by TestOwner. */
2450 inline bool IsOwnedBy( const AActor* TestOwner ) const
2451 {
2452 for( const AActor* Arg=this; Arg; Arg=Arg->Owner )
2453 {
2454 if( Arg == TestOwner )
2455 return true;
2456 }
2457 return false;
2458 }

3585 /**
3586 * Get Collision Response to the passed in Channel for all components
3587 * It returns Max of state - i.e. if Component A overlaps, but if Component B blocks, it will return block as response
3588 * if Component A ignores, but if Component B overlaps, it will return overlap
3589 */
3590 ENGINE_API virtual ECollisionResponse GetComponentsCollisionResponseToChannel(ECollisionChannel Channel) const;

3812
3813private:
3814
3815 /**
3816 * Internal helper function to call a compile-time lambda on all components of a given type
3817 * Use template parameter bClassIsActorComponent to avoid doing unnecessary IsA checks when the ComponentClass is exactly UActorComponent
3818 * Use template parameter bIncludeFromChildActors to recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those actors as well
3819 */
3820 template<class ComponentType, bool bClassIsActorComponent, bool bIncludeFromChildActors, typename Func>
3821 void ForEachComponent_Internal(TSubclassOf<UActorComponent> InComponentClass, Func InFunc) const
3822 {
3823 if (const UClass* ComponentClass = InComponentClass)
3824 {
3825 check(bClassIsActorComponent == false || ComponentClass == UActorComponent::StaticClass());
3826 check(ComponentClass->IsChildOf(ComponentType::StaticClass()));
3827
3828 // static check, so that the most common case (bIncludeFromChildActors) doesn't need to allocate an additional array :
3829 if (bIncludeFromChildActors)
3830 {
3831 TArray<AActor*, TInlineAllocator<NumInlinedActorComponents>> ChildActors;
3832 for (UActorComponent* OwnedComponent : OwnedComponents)
3833 {
3834 if (OwnedComponent)
3835 {
3836 if (bClassIsActorComponent || OwnedComponent->IsA(ComponentClass))
3837 {
3838 InFunc(static_cast<ComponentType *>(OwnedComponent));
3839 }
3840 if (UChildActorComponent* ChildActorComponent = Cast<UChildActorComponent>(OwnedComponent))
3841 {
3842 if (AActor* ChildActor = ChildActorComponent->GetChildActor())
3843 {
3844 ChildActors.Add(ChildActor);
3845 }
3846 }
3847 }
3848 }
3849
3850 for (AActor* ChildActor : ChildActors)
3851 {
3852 ChildActor->ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType, bClassIsActorComponent, bIncludeFromChildActors>(InComponentClass, InFunc);
3853 }
3854 }
3855 else
3856 {
3857 for (UActorComponent* OwnedComponent : OwnedComponents)
3858 {
3859 if (OwnedComponent)
3860 {
3861 if (bClassIsActorComponent || OwnedComponent->IsA(ComponentClass))
3862 {
3863 InFunc(static_cast<ComponentType *>(OwnedComponent));
3864 }
3865 }
3866 }
3867 }
3868 }
3869 }
3870
3871 /**
3872 * Internal helper function to call a compile-time lambda on all components of a given type
3873 * Redirects the call to the proper template function specialization for bClassIsActorComponent and bIncludeFromChildActors :
3874 */
3875 template<class ComponentType, typename Func>
3876 void ForEachComponent_Internal(TSubclassOf<UActorComponent> ComponentClass, bool bIncludeFromChildActors, Func InFunc) const
3877 {
3878 static_assert(TPointerIsConvertibleFromTo<ComponentType, const UActorComponent>::Value, "'ComponentType' template parameter to ForEachComponent must be derived from UActorComponent");
3879 if (ComponentClass == UActorComponent::StaticClass())
3880 {
3881 if (bIncludeFromChildActors)
3882 {
3883 ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType, true /*bClassIsActorComponent*/, true /*bIncludeFromChildActors*/>(ComponentClass, InFunc);
3884 }
3885 else
3886 {
3887 ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType, true /*bClassIsActorComponent*/, false /*bIncludeFromChildActors*/>(ComponentClass, InFunc);
3888 }
3889 }
3890 else
3891 {
3892 if (bIncludeFromChildActors)
3893 {
3894 ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType, false /*bClassIsActorComponent*/, true /*bIncludeFromChildActors*/>(ComponentClass, InFunc);
3895 }
3896 else
3897 {
3898 ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType, false /*bClassIsActorComponent*/, false /*bIncludeFromChildActors*/>(ComponentClass, InFunc);
3899 }
3900 }
3901 }
3902
3903public:
3904
3905 /**
3906 * Calls the compile-time lambda on each component of the specified type
3907 * @param ComponentType The component class to find all components of a class derived from
3908 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
3909 */
3910 template<class ComponentType, typename Func>
3911 void ForEachComponent(bool bIncludeFromChildActors, Func InFunc) const
3912 {
3913 ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType>(ComponentType::StaticClass(), bIncludeFromChildActors, InFunc);
3914 }
3915
3916 /**
3917 * Calls the compile-time lambda on each valid component
3918 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
3919 */
3920 template<typename Func>
3921 void ForEachComponent(bool bIncludeFromChildActors, Func InFunc) const
3922 {
3923 ForEachComponent_Internal<UActorComponent>(UActorComponent::StaticClass(), bIncludeFromChildActors, InFunc);
3924 }
3925
3926 /**
3927 * Get all components derived from specified ComponentClass and fill in the OutComponents array with the result.
3928 * It's recommended to use TArrays with a TInlineAllocator to potentially avoid memory allocation costs.
3929 * TInlineComponentArray is defined to make this easier, for example:
3930 * {
3931 * TInlineComponentArray<UPrimitiveComponent*> PrimComponents(Actor);
3932 * }
3933 *
3934 * @param ComponentClass The component class to find all components of a class derived from
3935 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
3936 */
3937 template<class AllocatorType, class ComponentType>
3938 void GetComponents(TSubclassOf<UActorComponent> ComponentClass, TArray<ComponentType*, AllocatorType>& OutComponents, bool bIncludeFromChildActors = false) const
3939 {
3940 OutComponents.Reset();
3941 ForEachComponent_Internal<ComponentType>(ComponentClass, bIncludeFromChildActors, [&](ComponentType* InComp)
3942 {
3943 OutComponents.Add(InComp);
3944 });
3945 }
3946
3947 /**
3948 * Get all components derived from class 'ComponentType' and fill in the OutComponents array with the result.
3949 * It's recommended to use TArrays with a TInlineAllocator to potentially avoid memory allocation costs.
3950 * TInlineComponentArray is defined to make this easier, for example:
3951 * {
3952 * TInlineComponentArray<UPrimitiveComponent*> PrimComponents(Actor);
3953 * }
3954 *
3955 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
3956 */
3957 template<class ComponentType, class AllocatorType>
3958 void GetComponents(TArray<ComponentType, AllocatorType>& OutComponents, bool bIncludeFromChildActors = false) const
3959 {
3960 typedef TPointedToType<ComponentType> T;
3961
3962 OutComponents.Reset();
3963 ForEachComponent_Internal<T>(T::StaticClass(), bIncludeFromChildActors, [&](T* InComp)
3964 {
3965 OutComponents.Add(InComp);
3966 });
3967 }
3968
3969 /**
3970 * Get all components derived from class 'ComponentType' and fill in the OutComponents array with the result.
3971 * It's recommended to use TArrays with a TInlineAllocator to potentially avoid memory allocation costs.
3972 * TInlineComponentArray is defined to make this easier, for example:
3973 * {
3974 * TInlineComponentArray<UPrimitiveComponent*> PrimComponents(Actor);
3975 * }
3976 *
3977 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
3978 */
3979 template<class T, class AllocatorType>
3980 void GetComponents(TArray<T*, AllocatorType>& OutComponents, bool bIncludeFromChildActors = false) const
3981 {
3982 // We should consider removing this function. It's not really hurting anything by existing but the one above it was added so that
3983 // we weren't assuming T*, preventing TObjectPtrs from working for this function. The only downside is all the people who force the
3984 // template argument with GetComponents's code suddenly not compiling with no clear error message.
3985
3986 OutComponents.Reset();
3987 ForEachComponent_Internal<T>(T::StaticClass(), bIncludeFromChildActors, [&](T* InComp)
3988 {
3989 OutComponents.Add(InComp);
3990 });
3991 }
3992
3993 /**
3994 * Get all components derived from class 'T' and fill in the OutComponents array with the result.
3995 * It's recommended to use TArrays with a TInlineAllocator to potentially avoid memory allocation costs.
3996 * TInlineComponentArray is defined to make this easier, for example:
3997 * {
3998 * TInlineComponentArray<UPrimitiveComponent*> PrimComponents(Actor);
3999 * }
4000 *
4001 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
4002 */
4003 template<class T, class AllocatorType>
4004 void GetComponents(TArray<TObjectPtr<T>, AllocatorType>& OutComponents, bool bIncludeFromChildActors = false) const
4005 {
4006 OutComponents.Reset();
4007 ForEachComponent_Internal<T>(T::StaticClass(), bIncludeFromChildActors, [&](T* InComp)
4008 {
4009 OutComponents.Add(InComp);
4010 });
4011 }
4012
4013 /**
4014 * UActorComponent specialization of GetComponents() to avoid unnecessary casts.
4015 * It's recommended to use TArrays with a TInlineAllocator to potentially avoid memory allocation costs.
4016 * TInlineComponentArray is defined to make this easier, for example:
4017 * {
4018 * TInlineComponentArray<UActorComponent*> PrimComponents;
4019 * Actor->GetComponents(PrimComponents);
4020 * }
4021 *
4022 * @param bIncludeFromChildActors If true then recurse in to ChildActor components and find components of the appropriate type in those Actors as well
4023 */
4024 template<class AllocatorType>
4025 void GetComponents(TArray<UActorComponent*, AllocatorType>& OutComponents, bool bIncludeFromChildActors = false) const
4026 {
4027 OutComponents.Reset();
4028 ForEachComponent_Internal<UActorComponent>(UActorComponent::StaticClass(), bIncludeFromChildActors, [&](UActorComponent* InComp)
4029 {
4030 OutComponents.Add(InComp);
4031 });
4032 }

4131 /**
4132 * Stop replicating a subobject and tell actor channels who spawned a replica of this subobject to release ownership over it.
4133 * This means that on the remote connection the network engine will stop holding a reference to the subobject and it's up to other systems
4134 * to keep that reference active or the subobject will get garbage collected.
4135 * Note that the subobject won't be replicated anymore, so it's final state on the client will be the one from the last replication update sent.
4136 * If you are using the legacy subobject replication method (ReplicateSubObjects() aka bReplicateUsingRegisteredSubObjectList=false) make sure the
4137 * subobject doesn't get replicated there either.
4138 * @param SubObject The SubObject to tear off
4139 */
4140 ENGINE_API void TearOffReplicatedSubObjectOnRemotePeers(UObject* SubObject);
4141
4142 /** Similar to the other tear off function but for subobjects owned by an ActorComponent */
4143 ENGINE_API void TearOffReplicatedSubObjectOnRemotePeers(UActorComponent* OwnerComponent, UObject* SubObject);
4144
4145 /**
4146 * Register a SubObject that will get replicated along with the actor component owning it.
4147 * The subobject needs to be manually removed from the list before it gets deleted.
4148 * @param SubObject The SubObject to replicate
4149 * @param NetCondition Optional condition to select which type of connection we will replicate the object to.
4150 */
4151 ENGINE_API void AddActorComponentReplicatedSubObject(UActorComponent* OwnerComponent, UObject* SubObject, ELifetimeCondition NetCondition = COND_None);
4152
4153 /**
4154 * Unregister a SubObject owned by an ActorComponent so it stops being replicated.
4155 * @param SubObject The SubObject to remove
4156 */
4157 ENGINE_API void RemoveActorComponentReplicatedSubObject(UActorComponent* OwnerComponent, UObject* SubObject);
4158
4159 /** Tells if the object has been registered as a replicated subobject of this actor */
4160 ENGINE_API bool IsReplicatedSubObjectRegistered(const UObject* SubObject) const;
4161
4162 /** Tells if the component has been registered as a replicated component */
4163 ENGINE_API bool IsReplicatedActorComponentRegistered(const UActorComponent* ReplicatedComponent) const;
4164
4165 /** Tells if an object owned by a component has been registered as a replicated subobject of the component */
4166 ENGINE_API bool IsActorComponentReplicatedSubObjectRegistered(const UActorComponent* OwnerComponent, const UObject* SubObject) const;

4169 /**
4170 * Fetches all the components of ActorClass's CDO, including the ones added via the BP editor (which AActor.GetComponents fails to do for CDOs).
4171 * @param InActorClass Class of AActor for which we will retrieve all components.
4172 * @param InComponentClass Only retrieve components of this type.
4173 * @param OutComponents this is where the found components will end up. Note that the preexisting contents of OutComponents will get overridden.
4174 */
4175 static ENGINE_API void GetActorClassDefaultComponents(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, const TSubclassOf<UActorComponent>& InComponentClass, TArray<const UActorComponent*>& OutComponents);
4176
4177 /**
4178 * Fetches the first component of ActorClass's CDO which match the requested component class. Will include the components added via the BP editor (which AActor.GetComponents fails to do for CDOs).
4179 * @param InActorClass Class of AActor for which we will retrieve all components.
4180 * @param InComponentClass Only retrieve components of this type.
4181 * @param OutComponents this is where the found components will end up. Note that the preexisting contents of OutComponents will get overridden.
4182 */
4183 static ENGINE_API const UActorComponent* GetActorClassDefaultComponent(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, const TSubclassOf<UActorComponent>& InComponentClass);
4184
4185 /**
4186 * Get the component of ActorClass's CDO that matches the given object name. Will consider all components, including the ones added via the BP editor (which AActor.GetComponents fails to do for CDOs).
4187 * @param InActorClass Class of AActor for which we will search all components.
4188 * @param InComponentClass Only consider components of this type.
4189 * @param OutComponents this is where the found components will end up. Note that the preexisting contents of OutComponents will get overridden.
4190 */
4191 static ENGINE_API const UActorComponent* GetActorClassDefaultComponentByName(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, const TSubclassOf<UActorComponent>& InComponentClass, FName InComponentName);
4192
4193 /**
4194 * Iterate over the components of ActorClass's CDO, including the ones added via the BP editor (which AActor.GetComponents fails to return).
4195 * @param InActorClass Class of AActor for which we will retrieve all components.
4196 * @param InComponentClass Only consider components of this type.
4197 * @param InFunc Code that will be executed for each component. Must return true to continue iteration, or false to stop.
4198 */
4199 static ENGINE_API void ForEachComponentOfActorClassDefault(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, const TSubclassOf<UActorComponent>& InComponentClass, TFunctionRef<bool(const UActorComponent*)> InFunc);
4200
4201 /**
4202 * Templated version of GetActorClassDefaultComponents()
4203 * @see GetActorClassDefaultComponents
4204 */
4205 template <typename TComponentClass = UActorComponent, typename = typename TEnableIf<TIsDerivedFrom<TComponentClass, UActorComponent>::IsDerived>::Type>
4206 static void GetActorClassDefaultComponents(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, TArray<const TComponentClass*>& OutComponents)
4207 {
4208 ForEachComponentOfActorClassDefault(InActorClass, TComponentClass::StaticClass(), [&](const UActorComponent* TemplateComponent)
4209 {
4210 OutComponents.Add(CastChecked<TComponentClass>(TemplateComponent));
4211 return true;
4212 });
4213 }
4214
4215 /**
4216 * Templated version of GetActorClassDefaultComponent()
4217 * @see GetActorClassDefaultComponent
4218 */
4219 template <typename TComponentClass = UActorComponent, typename = typename TEnableIf<TIsDerivedFrom<TComponentClass, UActorComponent>::IsDerived>::Type>
4220 static const TComponentClass* GetActorClassDefaultComponent(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass)
4221 {
4222 return Cast<TComponentClass>(GetActorClassDefaultComponent(InActorClass, TComponentClass::StaticClass()));
4223 }
4224
4225 /**
4226 * Templated version of GetActorClassDefaultComponentByName()
4227 * @see GetActorClassDefaultComponentByName
4228 */
4229 template <typename TComponentClass = UActorComponent, typename = typename TEnableIf<TIsDerivedFrom<TComponentClass, UActorComponent>::IsDerived>::Type>
4230 static const TComponentClass* GetActorClassDefaultComponentByName(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, FName InComponentName)
4231 {
4232 return Cast<TComponentClass>(GetActorClassDefaultComponentByName(InActorClass, TComponentClass::StaticClass(), InComponentName));
4233 }
4234
4235 /**
4236 * Templated version of ForEachComponentOfActorClassDefault()
4237 * @see ForEachComponentOfActorClassDefault
4238 */
4239 template <typename TComponentClass = UActorComponent, typename = typename TEnableIf<TIsDerivedFrom<TComponentClass, UActorComponent>::IsDerived>::Type>
4240 static void ForEachComponentOfActorClassDefault(const TSubclassOf<AActor>& InActorClass, TFunctionRef<bool(const TComponentClass*)> InFunc)
4241 {
4242 ForEachComponentOfActorClassDefault(InActorClass, TComponentClass::StaticClass(), [&](const UActorComponent* TemplateComponent)
4243 {
4244 return InFunc(CastChecked<TComponentClass>(TemplateComponent));
4245 });
4246 }

4311 /**
4312 * Trigger a noise caused by a given Pawn, at a given location.
4313 * Note that the NoiseInstigator Pawn MUST have a PawnNoiseEmitterComponent for the noise to be detected by a PawnSensingComponent.
4314 * Senders of MakeNoise should have an Instigator if they are not pawns, or pass a NoiseInstigator.
4315 *
4316 * @param Loudness The relative loudness of this noise. Usual range is 0 (no noise) to 1 (full volume). If MaxRange is used, this scales the max range, otherwise it affects the hearing range specified by the sensor.
4317 * @param NoiseInstigator Pawn responsible for this noise. Uses the actor's Instigator if NoiseInstigator is null
4318 * @param NoiseLocation Position of noise source. If zero vector, use the actor's location.
4319 * @param MaxRange Max range at which the sound may be heard. A value of 0 indicates no max range (though perception may have its own range). Loudness scales the range. (Note: not supported for legacy PawnSensingComponent, only for AIPerception)
4320 * @param Tag Identifier for the noise.
4321 */
4322 UFUNCTION(BlueprintCallable, BlueprintAuthorityOnly, Category="AI", meta=(BlueprintProtected = "true"))
4323 ENGINE_API void MakeNoise(float Loudness=1.f, APawn* NoiseInstigator=nullptr, FVector NoiseLocation=FVector::ZeroVector, float MaxRange = 0.f, FName Tag = NAME_None);
4324
4325 /** Default Implementation of MakeNoise */
4326 static ENGINE_API void MakeNoiseImpl(AActor* NoiseMaker, float Loudness, APawn* NoiseInstigator, const FVector& NoiseLocation, float MaxRange, FName Tag);
4327
4328 /** Modifies the global delegate used for handling MakeNoise */
4329 static ENGINE_API void SetMakeNoiseDelegate(const FMakeNoiseDelegate& NewDelegate);

4332 * Check if owned component should be relevant for navigation
4333 * Allows implementing master switch to disable e.g. collision export in projectiles

4335 virtual bool IsComponentRelevantForNavigation(UActorComponent* Component) const { return true; }

4819/** Helper function for executing component tick functions using the same conditions as FActorTickFunction */
4820template <typename ExecuteTickLambda>
4821void FActorComponentTickFunction::ExecuteTickHelper(UActorComponent* Target, bool bTickInEditor, float DeltaTime, ELevelTick TickType, const ExecuteTickLambda& ExecuteTickFunc)
4822{
4823 if (IsValid(Target))
4824 {
4825 FScopeCycleCounterUObject ComponentScope(Target);
4826 FScopeCycleCounterUObject AdditionalScope(Target->AdditionalStatObject());
4827
4828 if (Target->bRegistered)
4829 {
4830 AActor* MyOwner = Target->GetOwner();
4831 if (TickType != LEVELTICK_ViewportsOnly || bTickInEditor ||
4832 (MyOwner && MyOwner->ShouldTickIfViewportsOnly()))
4833 {
4834 const float TimeDilation = (MyOwner ? MyOwner->CustomTimeDilation : 1.f);
4835 ExecuteTickFunc(DeltaTime * TimeDilation);
4836 }
4837 }
4838 }
4839}
4840
4841template<class T, uint32 NumElements>
4842TInlineComponentArray<T, NumElements>::TInlineComponentArray(const AActor* Actor, bool bIncludeFromChildActors)
4843 : Super()
4844{
4845 if (Actor)
4846 {
4847 Actor->GetComponents(*this, bIncludeFromChildActors);
4848 }
4849};

4933FORCEINLINE_DEBUGGABLE ENetMode AActor::GetNetMode() const
4934{
4935 // IsRunningDedicatedServer() is a compile-time check in optimized non-editor builds.
4936 if (IsRunningDedicatedServer() && (NetDriverName == NAME_None || NetDriverName == NAME_GameNetDriver))
4937 {
4938 // Only normal net driver actors can have this optimization
4939 return NM_DedicatedServer;
4940 }
4941
4942 return InternalGetNetMode();
4943}
4944
4945FORCEINLINE_DEBUGGABLE bool AActor::IsNetMode(ENetMode Mode) const
4946{
4947#if UE_EDITOR
4948 // Editor builds are special because of PIE, which can run a dedicated server without the app running with -server.
4949 return GetNetMode() == Mode;
4950#else
4951 // IsRunningDedicatedServer() is a compile-time check in optimized non-editor builds.
4952 if (Mode == NM_DedicatedServer)
4953 {
4954 return IsRunningDedicatedServer();
4955 }
4956 else if (NetDriverName == NAME_None || NetDriverName == NAME_GameNetDriver)
4957 {
4958 // Only normal net driver actors can have this optimization
4959 return !IsRunningDedicatedServer() && (InternalGetNetMode() == Mode);
4960 }
4961 else
4962 {
4963 return (InternalGetNetMode() == Mode);
4964 }
4965#endif
4966}
